				\begin{document}$$(\overline{F{R}_{i}}-\overline{F{R}_{j}})/(\overline{F{R}_{i}}+\overline{F{R}_{j}})$$\end{document}(FRi¯−FRj¯)/(FRi¯+FRj¯), where FRi and FRj are mean firing rates of a neuron over time periods i and j (i < j), respectively, and \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
